  <h2>What is Open G?</h2>
  <p>
    In Open G the open strings ring out a G major chord: D–G–D–G–B–D. It's the
    sound of Keith Richards' Stones riffs, slide blues, and banjo-style
    fingerpicking. Barre one fret with a single finger and you have a full
    major chord anywhere on the neck.
  </p>
  <h2>How to tune to Open G</h2>
  <p>
    From standard, three strings drop a whole step: the low E to D, the A to G,
    and the high E to D. The D, G, and B strings in the middle don't move.
    Tap start, pluck one string at a time, and follow the needle — the tuner
    highlights which peg belongs to the string it hears and tells you which
    way the pitch needs to go.
  </p>
